LineComment.Text:
This is done with ladder code instead of bits in an alarm struct, so that: a) it is easy to see at a glance which alarms are part of the critical alarm (and when monitoring, which alarms are causing the critical alarm) b) alarms cannot be removed from the critical alarm by accidentally flipping a bit in a struct, only via code change
When adding alarms, please add into the correct group and keep each group ordered by alarm number. You will thank yourself later. It is easy to make a mess here, resist the urge!

AttributeList.Text: Critical alarms stop the machine normally.
All alarms that are not critical. Do not activate on critical alarm
Alarms do not stop the machine. Alarms in this group are not in the Critical Alarm group

Some critical alarms cause a fast stop, a middle ground between a regular shutdown and an emergency stop All alarms in this group should also be in the Critical Alarms list. The machine shuts down normally but with a faster ramp. See FB34.
Or set it from the state machine
Ack All when starting machine (don't touch)
